Package: statascii
Title: Create Stata-like Tables in the R Console
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Gustavo", "Velásquez", email = "gvelasq2github@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Author: Gustavo Velásquez [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Gustavo Velásquez <gvelasq2github@gmail.com>
Description: Create Stata-like tables in the R console, including right-aligned text, Stata-like padding, various Stata table formats (`oneway`, `twoway`, and `summary`), and Unicode box drawing characters. 'statascii()' borrows heavily from 'asciify()'. The 'asciify()' function was written by @gavinsimpson in StackOverflow (https://stackoverflow.com/questions/13011383) and GitHub Gist (https://gist.github.com/gavinsimpson). The 'statascii()' function was first written by @g-velasq in Github Gist (https://gist.github.com/g-velasq).
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/g-velasq/statascii
BugReports: https://github.com/g-velasq/statascii/issues
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.1)
Imports: 
    dplyr,
    magrittr,
    rlang,
    stringr
Suggests: 
    covr,
    testthat
ByteCompile: true
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
